Earlier, I joined my colleagues from Pennsylvania in a moment of silence on the House floor for three slain law enforcement officers - Detective Sergeant Cody Becker, Detective Mark Baker, and Detective Isaiah Emenheiser, all of the Northern York County Regional Police Department – who were killed in the line of duty on Wednesday. 

May God bless their families during this tragic time.

House Democrats have demanded $1.5 trillion in new spending to keep the government open for four weeks. Today, we did the responsible thing and passed a short-term extension, keeping the lights on through November 21st. 
It is up to the Senate to follow suit.

I am deeply disappointed in the Shapiro Administration’s decision to close SCI Rockview and the Quehanna Boot Camp, a move that will create serious financial and public safety challenges for Central Pennsylvania. 

Shuttering these facilities will not reduce the number of incarcerated individuals; it will simply shift larger inmate populations onto other institutions and impact nearly 900 corrections officers and staff. I urge the Governor to reconsider this dangerous decision.

On this day, we honor and remember the bravery of our 1.8 million Purple Heart recipients. 

As a proud father of a Purple Heart Wounded Warrior, I have witnessed firsthand the tremendous sacrifice service members and their families make to protect our country. Their bravery will never be forgotten.

As we celebrate the birth of our great nation, I want to wish you and your family a safe and joyful Fourth of July. Let us never forget the brave men and women who fought for our freedoms. Let's continue to honor their sacrifice by upholding the values of liberty and justice. May God bless you, and may God bless America.

This rant from @GovernorShapiro is nothing more than a smokescreen to distract from his administration's mismanagement. Under his leadership, Pennsylvania's SNAP error rates remained consistently high, hurting the very people the program is intended to help. His refusal to support the pathway to opportunity included in the Medicaid and SNAP reforms of the One Big Beautiful Bill shows a clear preference for dependency over dignity. Sadly, it's no surprise that liberals thrive on keeping people trapped in a cycle of poverty. It is shameful.

This week, I had the pleasure of meeting with students from Rock L. Butler Middle School in Wellsboro, who placed 5th in the nation in this year’s Capitol Hill Challenge! This 16-week financial education competition challenges students to invest a hypothetical $100,000, teaching them the power of the capital markets and the importance of financial literacy. Out of thousands of teams from across the country, these students stood out thanks to their hard work, teamwork, and sharp investing skills. Congratulations to the Rock L. Butler team on this incredible achievement!
